name: Ella's Foundation
review_text:
Ella's helped me get back on my feet. The lovely nurses and (most of the) staff really did their part to make sure that we are safe. I was disappointed, however, when management told me to fix my "snoring problem" or I would be back on the streets. I was then told that I could fix the problem if I wanted to, though my snoring was believed to be medical.

I was advised to play a didgeridoo to help with the snoring. Inappropriate to say the least. I don't think that a few bad apples should ruin the bunch, but unfortunately those bad apples were in management. Simple problems don't deserve life-threatening ultimatums and superficial solutions.

There were unnecessary, daily house meetings. The clients were also a bit strange, always making homophobic and racist remarks. I expected clients that had anger issues, drug addictions, and other mental concerns, but everyday felt like a circus at times.
